### **1. DNS/CDN Automation Script with AWS & Cloudflare APIs**  
#### **Cloudflare DNS Setup**  
```bash
#!/bin/bash

CF_API_TOKEN="your-cloudflare-api-token"
ZONES="codeximmortal.com"
ENDPOINT="api.cloudflare.com/client/v4/zones"

# Add A record for codeximmortal.com
curl -X POST "https://${ENDPOINT}" \
     -H "Authorization: Bearer $CF_API_TOKEN" \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"type":"A","name":"codeximmortal.com","content":"192.168.0.1","ttl":3600,"proxied":true}'

# Add WWW redirect to HTTPS
curl -X POST "https://${ENDPOINT}" \
     -H "Authorization: Bearer $CF_API_TOKEN" \
     -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
     -d '{"type":"CNAME","name":"www.codeximmortal.com","content":"central.netlify.app","proxied":true}'
```

#### **AWS CDN Integration (CloudFront + S3)**  
```bash
# 1. Create S3 Bucket for Static Files
aws s3 mb s3://codeximmortal.com --region us-east-1

# 2. Upload index.html
aws s3 cp index.html s3://codeximmortal.com/index.html

# 3. Create CloudFront Distribution
aws cloudfront create-distribution \
  --origin-domain-name codeximmortal.com.s3.amazonaws.com \
  --default-cache-behavior "{\"TargetOriginId\":\"codeximmortal.com-s3-origin\",\"ViewerProtocolPolicy\":\"redirect-to-https\"}" \
  --aliases codeximmortal.com
```

#### **Security Note**  
- Store API keys in `.env` files locally.  
- Use `aws configure` and `cloudflare` CLI tools for automation.  

